==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Coverlet
<hw>Cov"er*let</hw> <pr>(k?v"?r-l?t)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>couvre-lit</ets>; <ets>couvrir</ets> to cover + <ets>lit</ets> bed,
fr. L. <ets>lectus</ets> bed. See <er>Cover</er>.]</ety> <def>The
uppermost cover of a bed or of any piece of furniture.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Lay her in lilies and in violets . . . ⟦br⟧
And odored sheets and arras <qex>coverlets</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Coverlid</ent>⟦br⟧
